I made you a sandwich.

72
00:09:22,572 --> 00:09:24,875
Sit right here.

73
00:09:24,908 --> 00:09:26,576
I’m just gonna go take a quick look around.

74
00:09:26,610 --> 00:09:28,011
I’ll be right back.

75
00:10:28,006 --> 00:10:29,373
-[dog barking] -[car door closing]

76
00:10:31,043 --> 00:10:32,377
Good boy.

77
00:10:33,412 --> 00:10:34,379
I got ’em.

78
00:10:39,518 --> 00:10:40,986
Come on, boy.

79
00:10:41,019 --> 00:10:42,287
Oh.

80
00:10:46,326 --> 00:10:47,627
Who are you?

81
00:10:47,660 --> 00:10:49,561
What the hell are you doing in my house?

82
00:10:51,397 --> 00:10:52,832
Sorry.

83
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:56,202
We couldn’t wait, and he was hungry.

84
00:11:00,073 --> 00:11:03,676
I had a mind that was your truck down the road.

85
00:11:03,710 --> 00:11:04,878
Yep, that’s me.

86
00:11:04,911 --> 00:11:06,446
I ran out of gas.

87
00:11:06,479 --> 00:11:08,515
Luckily, you’re close by.

88
00:11:08,548 --> 00:11:10,183
Lucky me.

89
00:11:11,084 --> 00:11:12,585
I wanted you to meet my boy,

90
00:11:12,619 --> 00:11:15,054
and he wanted to meet you.

91
00:11:15,089 --> 00:11:17,090
Well, good, ’cause I ain't giving you a red cent.

92
00:11:17,123 --> 00:11:18,859
You still owe me from last time.

93
00:11:18,893 --> 00:11:21,060
That’s not what this is about, I swear.

94
00:11:23,831 --> 00:11:25,399
What’s your name?

95
00:11:27,868 --> 00:11:30,404
Oh, you’re looking at my bear.

96
00:11:31,605 --> 00:11:32,973
[growls]

97
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:37,845
That’s the last damn face that bear ever made.

98
00:11:37,879 --> 00:11:40,848
It happened right out there in the backyard.

99
00:11:40,881 --> 00:11:43,150
The dogs started barking and carrying on,

100
00:11:43,184 --> 00:11:45,886
and I looked up from the sink and there he was,

101
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:48,155
surrounded by all three of them dogs

102
00:11:48,189 --> 00:11:50,392
clawing and scratching at him.

103
00:11:50,425 --> 00:11:51,926
Before I could get my gun,

104
00:11:51,959 --> 00:11:55,063
he had already took out poor old Daisy and Petey.

105
00:11:55,096 --> 00:11:57,232
I felled him right there.

106
00:11:57,265 --> 00:11:59,935
One blast to the chest. Blam!

107
00:11:59,968 --> 00:12:01,336
So, you remember that.

108
00:12:03,905 --> 00:12:05,640
Don’t mess with my dogs.

109
00:12:07,409 --> 00:12:08,443
You wanna touch it?

110
00:12:12,614 --> 00:12:15,384
Well, he’s a regular Chatty Cathy, ain’t he?

111
00:12:17,252 --> 00:12:19,055
He’s had a rough time lately.

112
00:12:19,088 --> 00:12:20,089
Mm.

113
00:12:20,956 --> 00:12:24,060
That cowboy of yours do that?

114
00:12:24,093 --> 00:12:25,861
Why you ain’t never had enough sense

115
00:12:25,895 --> 00:12:27,463
to pick a good one, had ya?

116
00:12:28,464 --> 00:12:29,966
Your picker’s broken.

117
00:12:32,468 --> 00:12:33,769
You want some ice cream?

118
00:12:33,803 --> 00:12:35,304
Okay. Sure.

119
00:12:35,338 --> 00:12:37,440
[Tess] Well, that broke the levee.

120
00:12:37,473 --> 00:12:39,842
Tell me your name, I’ll go fix you some.

121
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:41,377
-Kipp. -Kipp.

122
00:12:41,410 --> 00:12:44,680
Well, Kipp, have a seat, and I’ll go fix it for ya.

123
00:12:44,714 --> 00:12:47,451
Uh-uh. I’ll do it myself.

124
00:12:52,823 --> 00:12:55,125
Might have seemed fit to call.

125
00:12:55,158 --> 00:12:56,759
I just...

126
00:12:56,792 --> 00:12:58,027
I don’t know.

127
00:12:58,060 --> 00:12:59,930
I figured it’d be better if we just showed up.

128
00:12:59,963 --> 00:13:02,032
I mean, if I called, you’d just say no.

129
00:13:02,065 --> 00:13:03,700
Oh, well, you got that right.

130
00:13:07,104 --> 00:13:09,306
-[cabinet closes] -Here.

131
00:13:09,339 --> 00:13:10,774
[sighs]

132
00:13:10,807 --> 00:13:12,442
Meet me in the parlor.

133
00:13:20,817 --> 00:13:22,954
Feel free to turn on the TV.

134
00:13:22,987 --> 00:13:25,656
I did. All channels are black and white.

135
00:13:25,689 --> 00:13:27,258
Well, I wouldn’t know.

136
00:13:27,292 --> 00:13:28,125
Colorblind.

137
00:13:28,158 --> 00:13:30,361
That’s very rare for a woman.

138
00:13:30,395 --> 00:13:31,462
Yeah.

139
00:13:33,064 --> 00:13:37,001
Well, I am a very rare woman.

140
00:13:38,303 --> 00:13:40,104
Dichromasy or Monochromasy?

141
00:13:40,138 --> 00:13:42,206
-What’d you say? -Two kinds of colorblindness.

142
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,574
They’re both hereditary.

143
00:13:43,608 --> 00:13:45,144
-Hm. -You know?

144
00:13:45,177 --> 00:13:46,978
No, I did not know.

145
00:13:48,179 --> 00:13:49,747
How’d you get so smart?

146
00:13:49,782 --> 00:13:50,948
How you know all that stuff?

147
00:13:50,983 --> 00:13:52,116
You got it too?

148
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:54,185
I’m not sure. Couldn’t know if I do.

149
00:13:54,218 --> 00:13:56,422
Now why would you say a thing like that?

150
00:13:56,455 --> 00:13:58,824
Well, some scientists say colorblindness could be

151
00:13:58,857 --> 00:14:00,659
an evolutionary advantage.

152
00:14:00,693 --> 00:14:02,127
Lots of animals are colorblind.

153
00:14:02,161 --> 00:14:04,830
Especially predators.

154
00:14:04,863 --> 00:14:06,131
And bears?

155
00:14:06,165 --> 00:14:07,967
No, bears can see in color.

156
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,301
Not anymore.

157
00:14:09,335 --> 00:14:11,103
[both laugh]

158
00:14:12,806 --> 00:14:15,507
You like that butter pecan, huh?

159
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:16,575
Yup.

160
00:14:16,608 --> 00:14:18,578
Just like your mama.

161
00:14:18,611 --> 00:14:20,813
She used to come home straight through that front door,

162
00:14:20,846 --> 00:14:22,415
head right to the deep freeze,

163
00:14:22,449 --> 00:14:26,286
and eat her way clean through all my favorite flavors.

164
00:14:26,319 --> 00:14:27,654
[Murel] Don’t eat too much, honey!

165
00:14:27,687 --> 00:14:29,254
You’ll spoil your appetite!

166
00:14:29,288 --> 00:14:30,190
[sighs]

167
00:14:30,223 --> 00:14:31,690
We staying for supper?

168
00:14:31,724 --> 00:14:33,526
Would you like to stay?

169
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,329
Do you want to?

170
00:14:35,363 --> 00:14:36,730
Mm.

171
00:14:58,185 --> 00:15:00,454
He certainly likes you.

172
00:15:00,487 --> 00:15:02,958
That’s the most he’s spoken in months.

173
00:15:02,990 --> 00:15:04,291
[bottle hisses]

174
00:15:05,726 --> 00:15:06,727
Mm.

175
00:15:10,064 --> 00:15:11,665
Well, let’s see.

176
00:15:11,699 --> 00:15:14,835
Last time I saw or heard from you was, what...

177
00:15:14,869 --> 00:15:16,604
seven, eight years ago?

178
00:15:18,139 --> 00:15:21,675
Looks like that money you stole from me

179
00:15:21,709 --> 00:15:25,646
you didn’t use it for what it was you said you was gonna do.

180
00:15:27,682 --> 00:15:28,884
No, I didn’t.

181
00:15:28,916 --> 00:15:29,951
[sighs]

182
00:15:29,985 --> 00:15:31,853
And thank the good Lord.

183
00:15:33,121 --> 00:15:34,890
He’s my little man.

184
00:15:34,923 --> 00:15:36,491
He’s my angel.

185
00:15:41,163 --> 00:15:43,165
Sorry I took that money from ya.

186
00:15:43,198 --> 00:15:45,767
I really am.

187
00:15:45,801 --> 00:15:47,603
I just...

188
00:15:47,637 --> 00:15:50,039
I just knew you wouldn’t lend it to me for that,

189
00:15:50,072 --> 00:15:52,442
and I had nowhere else to go.

190
00:15:53,443 --> 00:15:55,745
How do you know what I would’ve done?

191
00:15:55,778 --> 00:15:56,913
I’m a woman.

192
00:15:56,946 --> 00:15:58,815
I watch "The View."

193
00:16:02,952 --> 00:16:04,120
Where’s his daddy?

194
00:16:04,153 --> 00:16:06,155
His real daddy.

195
00:16:06,189 --> 00:16:07,957
What was his name?

196
00:16:07,990 --> 00:16:09,926
Chip? Chuck?

197
00:16:09,959 --> 00:16:11,561
Chet.

198
00:16:11,594 --> 00:16:12,663
Chet.

199
00:16:13,730 --> 00:16:15,132
Last I heard, he was

200
00:16:15,165 --> 00:16:17,301
holed up drunk and high in that same shithole

201
00:16:17,334 --> 00:16:19,469
trailer we used to live in.

202
00:16:19,502 --> 00:16:21,637
And the one who done all that to you?

203
00:16:24,675 --> 00:16:25,676
No.

204
00:16:25,709 --> 00:16:27,744
I know what you’re thinkin', Tess.

205
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:29,112
Tommy is different.

206
00:16:29,145 --> 00:16:30,781
He was good,

207
00:16:30,814 --> 00:16:32,149
and he is good.

208
00:16:32,182 --> 00:16:34,852
He’s really good when he’s not drinkin'.

209
00:16:34,885 --> 00:16:38,255
Yeah, I saw that big ol’ diamond ring on your finger.

210
00:16:40,591 --> 00:16:42,627
He loves me,

211
00:16:42,660 --> 00:16:45,263
and he loves Kipp.

212
00:16:45,296 --> 00:16:48,131
He insisted on adopting Kipp right after we got married.

213
00:16:48,165 --> 00:16:49,600
Chet didn’t even put up a fight.

214
00:16:49,634 --> 00:16:52,770
Then one day out of the blue, Tommy just smacks you a good one

215
00:16:52,804 --> 00:16:54,304
on his way to feed the homeless.

216
00:16:55,907 --> 00:16:57,709
That what happened, Murel?

217
00:16:57,742 --> 00:16:58,743
Hm?

218
00:17:00,512 --> 00:17:02,080
And the boy?

219
00:17:02,113 --> 00:17:04,282
Does his new daddy beat him?

220
00:17:05,116 --> 00:17:06,150
No.

221
00:17:06,184 --> 00:17:07,385
Hell no.

222
00:17:07,418 --> 00:17:10,189
I’d kill him if he ever laid a hand on him.

223
00:17:10,222 --> 00:17:12,290
What’s the police say about all this?

224
00:17:12,323 --> 00:17:14,792
They don’t see me as nothing but a kooky bird.

225
00:17:14,827 --> 00:17:16,794
[sighs]

226
00:17:16,828 --> 00:17:18,731
So where you gonna go?

227
00:17:22,568 --> 00:17:24,102
Hell, I just wanna go somewhere

228
00:17:24,135 --> 00:17:25,871
there’s a crowd I can get lost in.

229
00:17:25,905 --> 00:17:26,872
Hm.

230
00:17:53,165 --> 00:17:54,300
[Murel] What is this?

231
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:55,869
-[Kipp] The sun. -[Murel] Oh, yeah?

232
00:17:55,902 --> 00:17:57,137
[Kipp] It’s like... [hums]

233
00:17:57,170 --> 00:17:58,238
somewhere.

234
00:17:58,271 --> 00:18:00,040
From California.

235
00:18:00,073 --> 00:18:02,409
[hums]

236
00:18:03,909 --> 00:18:05,045
And what’s this?

237
00:18:05,078 --> 00:18:07,180
A seashell from California.

238
00:18:07,214 --> 00:18:09,549
[hums]

239
00:18:09,583 --> 00:18:11,818
We’re invading the picture.

240
00:18:11,851 --> 00:18:13,987
-We’re invading the picture. -That’s the beach.

241
00:18:14,020 --> 00:18:15,122
Good.

242
00:18:15,156 --> 00:18:16,656
I don’t even know what a mussel is though.

243
00:18:16,690 --> 00:18:19,560
When we get to California, we’ll go find one.

244
00:18:20,594 --> 00:18:22,563
How about we put this stuff up now?

245
00:18:22,597 --> 00:18:23,397
No.

246
00:18:23,431 --> 00:18:24,865
Put your ship in.

247
00:18:24,899 --> 00:18:27,335
-Okay. -There you go.

248
00:18:27,368 --> 00:18:29,604
I’m a little bit nervous about the earthquakes.

249
00:18:29,637 --> 00:18:32,239
They say it isn’t if, it’s when, you know.

250
00:18:32,273 --> 00:18:34,308
Oh. Well...

251
00:18:34,342 --> 00:18:36,344
don’t you worry, baby boy.

252
00:18:36,377 --> 00:18:38,613
We’ll get us a house on roller skates,

253
00:18:38,646 --> 00:18:41,983
and when the big one comes, we’ll just roll all around.

254
00:18:42,016 --> 00:18:44,352
[both laugh]

255
00:18:50,792 --> 00:18:53,495
Sweetheart, Kipp...

256
00:18:54,930 --> 00:18:56,564
has Daddy ever hit you?

257
00:18:58,233 --> 00:19:00,469
No, Mama. Why?

258
00:19:02,604 --> 00:19:03,738
Good.

259
00:19:10,013 --> 00:19:11,546
Eskimo kiss?

260
00:19:16,052 --> 00:19:17,854
So, till...

261
00:19:17,886 --> 00:19:21,289
[both] jellyfish walk and turtles fly,

262
00:19:21,323 --> 00:19:24,827
unicorns fart and eat booger pies,

263
00:19:24,861 --> 00:19:29,465
till gators drive cars and dolphins take flight,

264
00:19:29,499 --> 00:19:31,868
I love you, I love you

265
00:19:31,901 --> 00:19:35,172
-till morning. Good night. -I love... morning. Good night.

266
00:19:35,205 --> 00:19:36,973
[kisses] Oh!

267
00:19:37,006 --> 00:19:39,042
What was that?

268
00:19:39,075 --> 00:19:40,610
What the heck?

269
00:19:41,444 --> 00:19:42,846
Was that your tongue?

270
00:19:42,879 --> 00:19:45,015
Gross! Ew!

271
00:19:45,049 --> 00:19:47,084
-Ew! -[laughs]

272
00:19:47,117 --> 00:19:48,851
Yuck!

273
00:19:48,885 --> 00:19:50,788
Inappropriate!

274
00:19:50,821 --> 00:19:52,922
