818
00:54:25,629 --> 00:54:27,030
Are you okay?

819
00:54:27,063 --> 00:54:29,066
Baby, are you okay?

820
00:54:29,099 --> 00:54:30,968
Asshole. What an idiot!

821
00:54:31,001 --> 00:54:33,103
Oh, God. Get up here.

822
00:54:33,137 --> 00:54:35,206
Asshole!

823
00:54:35,239 --> 00:54:36,607
Yes.

824
00:54:36,640 --> 00:54:38,577
He’s a real a-hole.

825
00:54:38,609 --> 00:54:40,679
Although, I don’t want you using that word.

826
00:54:53,458 --> 00:54:55,594
I’m hungry!

827
00:54:55,627 --> 00:54:58,463
Well, I saw a Denny’s down the road.

828
00:54:58,496 --> 00:55:02,334
I am not getting back in that bag tonight.

829
00:55:02,367 --> 00:55:03,503
Okay, fine.

830
00:55:03,536 --> 00:55:05,237
Fine. I can understand that.

831
00:55:07,472 --> 00:55:09,408
I saw a bar next door.

832
00:55:09,442 --> 00:55:10,676
What if I just go over there

833
00:55:10,710 --> 00:55:12,744
and see if they got some food too?

834
00:55:13,879 --> 00:55:15,347
Okay, stay here and watch TV.

835
00:55:15,381 --> 00:55:16,582
I’ll be right back.

836
00:55:16,616 --> 00:55:18,084
Do not open for anybody

837
00:55:18,117 --> 00:55:19,918
and don’t leave the room, you got it?

838
00:55:21,152 --> 00:55:23,755
Good. Lock this door.

839
00:55:23,789 --> 00:55:24,923
Lock it.

840
00:55:24,956 --> 00:55:26,025
Baby.

841
00:55:31,597 --> 00:55:33,099
[Kipp] Milkshake!

842
00:55:34,300 --> 00:55:35,301
Chocolate!

843
00:55:35,334 --> 00:55:37,303
-Shh! -No! Strawberry!

844
00:55:37,336 --> 00:55:38,738
Goodness.

845
00:55:39,805 --> 00:55:41,875
♪ Sing along ♪

846
00:55:41,909 --> 00:55:47,313
♪ If I could write you a song ♪

847
00:55:47,346 --> 00:55:51,485
♪ With Jesus ♪

848
00:55:51,518 --> 00:55:53,586
-Oh, excuse me. Sorry. -♪ Oh ♪

849
00:55:59,860 --> 00:56:01,562
Excuse me, can I get a menu?

850
00:56:01,595 --> 00:56:03,364
-Sure. -And a beer.

851
00:56:03,398 --> 00:56:04,398
Thanks.

852
00:56:04,431 --> 00:56:05,432
[cheering and applause]

853
00:56:05,465 --> 00:56:06,833
Well, thank you very much.

854
00:56:06,867 --> 00:56:08,936
This next little number, the one I wrote,

855
00:56:08,969 --> 00:56:11,638
I’d like to dedicate to the... the pretty lady

856
00:56:11,672 --> 00:56:13,674
from Oklahoma City who just walked through the door.

857
00:56:27,220 --> 00:56:30,058
♪ Look at all the roads I’ve taken ♪

858
00:56:30,091 --> 00:56:33,329
♪ Some of them even left me shaking ♪

859
00:56:33,362 --> 00:56:34,529
♪ Battered and... ♪

860
00:56:34,562 --> 00:56:35,931
[television chatter]

861
00:56:55,517 --> 00:56:58,420
♪ But I made it on through ♪

862
00:56:58,453 --> 00:56:59,955
♪ You always ♪

863
00:56:59,989 --> 00:57:01,924
-[television chatter] -[door unlocking]

864
00:57:14,536 --> 00:57:15,904
♪ Home ♪

865
00:57:19,575 --> 00:57:21,010
[cheering and applause]

866
00:57:21,043 --> 00:57:22,011
Thank you.

867
00:57:46,670 --> 00:57:47,872
Hey, can I buy you a beer?

868
00:57:47,905 --> 00:57:49,572
No, thank you. I already got one.

869
00:57:49,606 --> 00:57:51,342
Yeah, well, let’s get you another one

870
00:57:51,375 --> 00:57:52,610
before that one gets warm.

871
00:57:52,643 --> 00:57:53,811
[scoffs]

872
00:57:53,844 --> 00:57:55,979
Honestly, thank you, but I can’t.

873
00:57:56,012 --> 00:57:57,648
I left my son in the room.

874
00:57:57,682 --> 00:57:59,850
♪ Beautiful heart ♪

875
00:57:59,884 --> 00:58:01,685
♪ Beautiful soul ♪

876
00:58:01,719 --> 00:58:04,188
You know what? You can have my beer. Thanks.

877
00:58:04,221 --> 00:58:06,157
Well, now, hold on a second. Where are you going?

878
00:58:06,190 --> 00:58:07,024
Are you kidding me?

879
00:58:07,058 --> 00:58:09,493
The second I said the word "son,"

880
00:58:09,527 --> 00:58:12,463
your face turned 16 shades of white.

881
00:58:14,099 --> 00:58:15,300
No offense.

882
00:58:15,333 --> 00:58:17,669
It ain’t the first time I’ve seen a man get all pasty

883
00:58:17,702 --> 00:58:19,870
at the mention of a kid.

884
00:58:19,904 --> 00:58:21,972
You got a kid. Do you got a husband too?

885
00:58:22,006 --> 00:58:23,141
♪ Take it all in stride ♪

886
00:58:23,175 --> 00:58:25,577
♪ This crazy ride we’re on ♪

887
00:58:25,610 --> 00:58:27,979
Mm, a long story.

888
00:58:28,013 --> 00:58:29,748
Well, your food ain’t come yet.

889
00:58:29,781 --> 00:58:30,949
♪ Lose my breath ♪

890
00:58:30,982 --> 00:58:33,452
♪ Just like the day we met ♪

891
00:58:34,553 --> 00:58:36,321
-One beer. -Just one beer.

892
00:58:36,354 --> 00:58:38,124
-Fair? -That’s fair.

893
00:58:38,157 --> 00:58:39,292
Okay. Cheers.

894
00:58:39,325 --> 00:58:42,060
♪ My love for you will never change ♪

895
00:58:54,173 --> 00:58:55,174
[thud]

896
00:59:09,122 --> 00:59:10,424
Do you sing here all the time?

897
00:59:10,457 --> 00:59:12,558
Yeah. When I ain’t workin’ the grill.

898
00:59:12,592 --> 00:59:13,793
Well, you got a nice voice.

899
00:59:13,826 --> 00:59:14,927
Well, thank you.

900
00:59:14,961 --> 00:59:16,362
You like my songs?

901
00:59:16,396 --> 00:59:17,530
[chuckles]

902
00:59:17,563 --> 00:59:19,133
The one I heard was great.

903
00:59:19,166 --> 00:59:20,766
-Well, thank you very much. -Thank you.

904
00:59:20,800 --> 00:59:22,436
-Thanks for the dedication. -Yeah.

905
00:59:22,469 --> 00:59:24,138
♪ Beautiful heart ♪

906
00:59:24,171 --> 00:59:26,406
How come you think I’m from Oklahoma City?

907
00:59:27,474 --> 00:59:30,911
I don’t know. You just got that... that air.

908
00:59:30,944 --> 00:59:32,646
-That air? -Yeah.

909
00:59:32,679 --> 00:59:34,748
What does that mean, "that air"?

910
00:59:34,781 --> 00:59:36,517
-I’m full of air? -No! I don’t mean it bad.

911
00:59:36,550 --> 00:59:37,818
I just mean that you...

912
00:59:37,851 --> 00:59:39,620
you seem so experienced.

913
00:59:39,653 --> 00:59:42,556
Oh, thanks a lot. Jeez.

914
00:59:42,589 --> 00:59:43,690
I ain’t that old.

915
00:59:43,724 --> 00:59:45,593
No, no, that’s not what I mean at all.

916
00:59:45,627 --> 00:59:47,427
I just... oh, God.

917
00:59:47,461 --> 00:59:49,930
I’ve got a bad case of foot-in-mouth disease, I’m sorry.

918
00:59:51,833 --> 00:59:52,867
Can I try again?

919
00:59:52,901 --> 00:59:55,203
You’re already two for three.

920
00:59:55,236 --> 00:59:57,104
Man.

921
00:59:57,137 --> 01:00:00,408
Listen, I’m not from Oklahoma City.

922
01:00:00,441 --> 01:00:04,579
I’m just a small-town girl from Choctaw.

923
01:00:04,612 --> 01:00:06,014
Oh.

924
01:00:07,682 --> 01:00:08,850
Thank you.

925
01:00:08,883 --> 01:00:11,019
Well, uh, thanks for the beer.

926
01:00:11,052 --> 01:00:12,220
-Yeah. -And the music.

927
01:00:13,055 --> 01:00:14,956
Uh, you staying at The Glancy?

928
01:00:14,989 --> 01:00:16,792
I finish my last set at 11:00.

929
01:00:16,825 --> 01:00:17,860
Can I stop by and see you?

930
01:00:17,893 --> 01:00:20,262
You’re sweet, but, uh...

931
01:00:20,296 --> 01:00:22,163
we got an early start in the mornin’.

932
01:00:23,331 --> 01:00:24,632
♪ Beautiful ♪

933
01:00:24,666 --> 01:00:25,833
Me and the kid.

934
01:00:25,867 --> 01:00:27,803
[laughs] Okay.

935
01:00:27,836 --> 01:00:29,038
I’m getting better, see?

936
01:00:29,071 --> 01:00:30,506
I didn’t turn all white that time.

937
01:00:30,539 --> 01:00:31,507
-Nice. -Yeah.

938
01:00:41,518 --> 01:00:43,053
They had chicken fried steak.

939
01:00:44,321 --> 01:00:45,422
Kipp?

940
01:00:46,590 --> 01:00:47,624
Kipp?

941
01:00:48,657 --> 01:00:49,658
Kipp?

942
01:00:49,692 --> 01:00:51,894
What are you doing under the bed?

943
01:00:51,927 --> 01:00:53,063
[sniffles]

944
01:00:53,096 --> 01:00:55,698
By the way, that guy came back.

945
01:00:55,731 --> 01:00:56,766
What guy?

946
01:00:56,800 --> 01:00:59,169
The jerk who dropped me on my head.

947
01:01:00,871 --> 01:01:01,870
Did he see you?

948
01:01:01,905 --> 01:01:03,974
No. I hid under here.

949
01:01:06,343 --> 01:01:07,477
Okay, good.

950
01:01:10,213 --> 01:01:12,015
Oh, you know what, sweetheart?

951
01:01:12,048 --> 01:01:14,252
I think he just wanted to bring us something nice.

952
01:01:15,885 --> 01:01:17,555
Guess what I brought for you?

953
01:01:20,790 --> 01:01:22,092
Are you hungry?

954
01:01:36,874 --> 01:01:38,142
[knocking]

955
01:01:45,583 --> 01:01:46,585
Hey.

956
01:01:46,618 --> 01:01:49,587
So I brought you that honeymoon suite champagne

957
01:01:49,620 --> 01:01:52,023
even though you ain’t in the honeymoon suite.

958
01:01:52,056 --> 01:01:53,291
Yes. Thank you so much.

959
01:01:53,324 --> 01:01:54,660
-That was so sweet of you. -Yeah.

960
01:01:54,693 --> 01:01:57,462
You know, I just thought that maybe... maybe you and me

961
01:01:57,496 --> 01:01:58,630
-could enjoy it. -Oh, no.

962
01:01:58,664 --> 01:01:59,865
Thank you.

963
01:01:59,898 --> 01:02:01,667
I’m just... gonna turn in.

964
01:02:01,700 --> 01:02:04,836
Come on. C... couldn’t you use a little company?

965
01:02:04,870 --> 01:02:07,005
A pretty gal like you...

966
01:02:07,039 --> 01:02:08,573
all alone.

967
01:02:08,607 --> 01:02:09,741
No, no.

968
01:02:09,775 --> 01:02:11,243
Really, I’m so tired.

969
01:02:11,276 --> 01:02:12,344
I’m just gonna hit the hay.

970
01:02:12,377 --> 01:02:15,580
You are... alone, aren’t you?

971
01:02:16,616 --> 01:02:17,650
Good night, Wade.

972
01:02:51,018 --> 01:02:55,089
[no discernible dialog]

973
01:03:06,066 --> 01:03:07,902
[Murel] I can explain!

974
01:03:07,936 --> 01:03:09,870
-Please don’t... Kipp! -Come on!

975
01:03:09,903 --> 01:03:11,473
Kipp! Ow!

976
01:03:11,506 --> 01:03:13,107
-Kipp! -[police radio chatter]

977
01:03:13,140 --> 01:03:14,942
Let go of me! No! Kipp!

978
01:03:14,975 --> 01:03:16,444
Kipp! Kipp!

979
01:03:18,011 --> 01:03:19,613
No. No.

980
01:03:19,646 --> 01:03:20,581
No!

981
01:03:20,614 --> 01:03:22,417
Listen to me. You have to listen to me.

982
01:03:22,450 --> 01:03:24,418
Not that man. You can’t let him take him.

983
01:03:25,420 --> 01:03:27,455
-No! Please! -[Wade] That’s her.

984
01:03:27,489 --> 01:03:30,658
Yeah, crazy lady carried her boy around in a bag!

985
01:03:30,692 --> 01:03:32,894
-No! -In a bag!

986
01:03:32,927 --> 01:03:34,196
He touched my son.

987
01:03:34,230 --> 01:03:36,431
He molested my son. You can’t let him take him.

988
01:03:36,464 --> 01:03:37,800
[sirens wail]

989
01:03:37,833 --> 01:03:40,068
Baby! It’s gonna be okay, baby!

990
01:03:40,101 --> 01:03:41,169
Don’t you do this.

991
01:03:41,202 --> 01:03:42,872
Don’t you fucking do this.

992
01:03:42,905 --> 01:03:44,472
Stop it! No!

993
01:03:44,506 --> 01:03:45,607
[Tommy] What’s wrong with you?

994
01:03:45,640 --> 01:03:47,576
I told you what I’d do and told her.

995
01:03:47,610 --> 01:03:48,744
Didn’t I tell you?

996
01:03:50,612 --> 01:03:52,013
Kipp, you all right, son?

997
01:03:52,046 --> 01:03:53,348
[Tommy] Shh. It’s okay.

998
01:03:53,382 --> 01:03:55,985
She’s gone. She can’t hurt you no more.

999
01:03:56,018 --> 01:03:58,654
He’s fine. Scared.

1000
01:03:58,687 --> 01:04:00,189
Tired.

1001
01:04:01,758 --> 01:04:03,225
I’m just glad he's safe.

1002
01:04:10,766 --> 01:04:11,834
[Murel] Please.

1003
01:04:11,867 --> 01:04:13,069
Please, you’ve got to help me.

1004
01:04:13,102 --> 01:04:14,804
You’ve got to help me! Please!

1005
01:04:14,837 --> 01:04:16,740
Please! I’m begging you! Please!

1006
01:04:16,773 --> 01:04:18,374
[sobs] Not him!

1007
01:04:18,407 --> 01:04:19,708
You can’t let him go with him.

1008
01:04:21,811 --> 01:04:23,380
Now you don’t have a mama.

1009
01:04:23,413 --> 01:04:25,215
What do think about that, you little shit?

1010
01:04:25,248 --> 01:04:26,716
You’ve got to help me!

1011
01:04:26,750 --> 01:04:28,017
This is not right!

1012
01:04:28,050 --> 01:04:30,353
-You’ve gotta listen to me. -Who’s gonna tuck you in now?

1013
01:04:32,689 --> 01:04:34,024
[siren wails]

1014
01:04:34,057 --> 01:04:35,425
[no discernible dialog]

1015
01:05:17,603 --> 01:05:19,604
[door buzzing]

1016
01:05:23,909 --> 01:05:25,443
I gotta get my boy back.

1017
01:05:25,476 --> 01:05:26,578
[sighs]

1018
01:05:30,048 --> 01:05:31,684
Come on. Sit down.

1019
01:05:34,120 --> 01:05:35,787
Hon, I can’t get you out of here.

1020
01:05:35,821 --> 01:05:37,389
Not right now.

1021
01:05:37,422 --> 01:05:38,992
They’ve got you on what they call

1022
01:05:39,025 --> 01:05:42,027
a 48-hour mental health hold.

1023
01:05:42,060 --> 01:05:43,529
What d... what do you mean?

1024
01:05:43,562 --> 01:05:45,764
Tommy told the court that he’s afraid

1025
01:05:45,797 --> 01:05:47,966
you’d hurt yourself, so they invoked a hold.

1026
01:05:48,000 --> 01:05:49,068
He can’t do that!

1027
01:05:49,102 --> 01:05:50,103
-Yeah. -How did he do that?

1028
01:05:50,136 --> 01:05:53,105
Yeah, they can. It’s the law.

1029
01:05:53,138 --> 01:05:54,841
This is not about the law, Randall.

1030
01:05:54,874 --> 01:05:57,776
This is about a mother’s rights to protect her kid.

1031
01:05:57,809 --> 01:06:01,047
This is about my right to protect my kid.

1032
01:06:01,080 --> 01:06:03,483
[knocking]

1033
01:06:05,585 --> 01:06:07,921
Randall, please, you’ve got to get me out of here.

1034
01:06:12,325 --> 01:06:15,029
So, truthfully now...

1035
01:06:15,062 --> 01:06:18,699
how long has this been goin’ on, what Tommy’s doing to Kipp?

1036
01:06:22,835 --> 01:06:23,837
Uh...

1037
01:06:25,538 --> 01:06:26,974
I don’t... I don't know.

1038
01:06:29,176 --> 01:06:30,578
But even if it’s only happened

1039
01:06:30,611 --> 01:06:32,513
once or twice, it can never happen again.

1040
01:06:32,546 --> 01:06:35,282
It can’t ever happen again.

1041
01:06:35,316 --> 01:06:36,451
Tommy could do all kinds

1042
01:06:36,484 --> 01:06:39,020
of terrible things to Kipp in 48 hours.

1043
01:06:40,421 --> 01:06:42,156
You think about that, Randall.

1044
01:06:42,189 --> 01:06:44,491
You think about that.

1045
01:06:47,728 --> 01:06:48,997
48 hours.

1046
01:06:49,030 --> 01:06:50,031
Two days.

1047
01:06:50,065 --> 01:06:51,865
Behave yourself.

1048
01:06:51,899 --> 01:06:54,703
You locked up the wrong person, Randall.

1049
01:06:57,272 --> 01:06:59,507
You locked up the wrong person!

1050
01:06:59,541 --> 01:07:00,542
[buzzing]

1051
01:07:04,113 --> 01:07:05,146
[door closes]

1052
01:07:05,180 --> 01:07:07,816
You locked up the wrong person!

1053
01:07:09,918 --> 01:07:11,152
[woman] That was awful.

1054
01:07:11,186 --> 01:07:12,354
[overlapping chatter]

1055
01:08:14,651 --> 01:08:16,853
Wow, you look like you was rode hard

1056
01:08:16,887 --> 01:08:18,121
and put away wet.

1057
01:08:20,091 --> 01:08:21,059
Hey.

1058
01:08:41,979 --> 01:08:43,514
-[sighs] -Okay.

1059
01:08:43,549 --> 01:08:45,216
You posted my bail?

1060
01:08:45,249 --> 01:08:46,518
How?

1061
01:08:46,552 --> 01:08:47,785
Well, never you mind.

1062
01:08:47,819 --> 01:08:49,487
Just don’t go jumpin' it, okay?

1063
01:08:49,521 --> 01:08:50,621
Where’s Kipp?

1064
01:08:50,655 --> 01:08:53,158
[sighs] Oh, honey, he’s at Tommy's.

1065
01:08:54,292 --> 01:08:55,460
Well, I gotta see him.

1066
01:08:55,493 --> 01:08:57,529
Let’s go see him. Can you take me there?

1067
01:09:00,599 --> 01:09:02,835
He’s got a restraining order against ya.

1068
01:09:02,868 --> 01:09:04,937
He can’t do that. He’s my son.

1069
01:09:04,970 --> 01:09:08,107
500 feet from both of ’em till this thing goes to trial.

1070
01:09:09,909 --> 01:09:10,909
No.

1071
01:09:10,943 --> 01:09:12,644
No! The hell with that!

1072
01:09:12,678 --> 01:09:15,180
I’m sorry, no law gonna keep me away from my boy.

1073
01:09:15,214 --> 01:09:16,483
-No! -Tess!

1074
01:09:16,516 --> 01:09:17,683
Not here, okay?

1075
01:09:17,716 --> 01:09:19,519
Let’s just go to Tommy's.

1076
01:09:19,552 --> 01:09:22,222
If you take me over to Tommy’s, we’ll work it out.

1077
01:09:22,255 --> 01:09:23,890
[Tess] I’ll get my purse out...

1078
01:09:30,697 --> 01:09:34,135
[no discernible dialog]

1079
01:09:52,685 --> 01:09:53,854
When Randall told me,

1080
01:09:53,888 --> 01:09:56,257
I nearly got my shotgun and went after that

1081
01:09:56,290 --> 01:09:58,225
dumb son of a bitch myself!

1082
01:10:00,327 --> 01:10:04,598
We’re both working on getting somebody to look into it for us,

